  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Socially inclusive policies in the area of disability inclusive development, youth and sport in the Pacific</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Inclusive &amp; evidence-based policies have been widely recognized by the Pacific SIDS as critical to addressing increasingly complex development outlook such as vulnerabilities of young people, exclusion of persons with disabilities (PWDs), and structural inequality. In addressing these challenges, regional frameworks were endorsed to guide policy and programme implementation including the Pacific Framework for the Rights of PWDs 2016 - 2025, the Pacific Youth Development Framework 2014-2023 &amp; the outcome statements of the Pacific Sport Minister meeting 2017. The project supports formulating and reviewing policies in the area of disability inclusive development, youth and sport. It builds on the existing UNESCO tools such as the Inclusive Policy Lab, and the Sport Policy Follow up Framework.</narrative>
  </description>
